article.description: Jayvon Graves had 15 points to lead five Buffalo players in double figures as the Bulls topped Miami (Ohio) 75-69 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Buffalo has 5 in double figures, beats Miami (Ohio) 75-69
article.linkText: Buffalo has 5 in double figures, beats Miami (Ohio) 75-69
article.story: BUFFALO, N.Y. -- Jayvon Graves had 15 points to lead five Buffalo players in double figures as the Bulls topped Miami (Ohio) 75-69 on Tuesday night. Davonta Jordan added 11 points for the Bulls. Josh Mballa, Gabe Grant and Antwain Johnson each chipped in 10 points. Jordan also had six assists, while Mballa posted 14 rebounds. Mekhi Lairy and Nike Sibande scored 13 points apiece for the RedHawks (12-18, 5-12 Mid-American Conference). Isaiah Coleman-Lands had 10 points. The Bulls improve to 2-0 against the RedHawks on the season. Buffalo defeated Miami (Ohio) 83-78 on Jan. 10. Buffalo (19-11, 10-7) finishes out the regular season against Bowling Green on the road on Friday. Miami (Ohio) finishes out the regular season against Ohio at home on Friday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
